.TH "SELFCERT" "1" "March 2026" "" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
selfcert \- generate a local CA and a leaf certificate bundle with
OpenSSL
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f[B]selfcert\f[R] [\-h] [\-d domain] [\-o org] [\-y days] [\-O
output_dir] [\-p pfx_password] [\-s san_list]
.SH DESCRIPTION
\f[B]selfcert\f[R] creates a small local certificate authority and a
leaf certificate for a target domain.
It writes a CA key and certificate, a serial file, the leaf private key
and CSR, the signed leaf certificate, and a PKCS#12 bundle.
.PP
The requested domain is always included in the certificate Subject
Alternative Name list.
Additional SAN entries can be supplied with \f[B]\-s\f[R].
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\f[B]\-d\f[R] domain
Domain name for the leaf certificate and output filenames.
Default: \f[CR]localhost\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]\-o\f[R] org
Organization and Common Name for the generated CA certificate.
Default: \f[CR]localhost\-ca\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]\-y\f[R] days
Validity period, in days, for both the CA and the leaf certificate.
Default: \f[CR]365\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]\-O\f[R] output_dir
Directory where generated files should be written.
Default: current directory.
.TP
\f[B]\-p\f[R] pfx_password
Password to use when exporting the PKCS#12 bundle.
If omitted, OpenSSL prompts interactively.
.TP
\f[B]\-s\f[R] san_list
Comma\-separated list of additional DNS subjectAltName entries.
The primary domain from \f[B]\-d\f[R] is always included.
.TP
\f[B]\-h\f[R]
Show usage help and exit.
.SH OUTPUT FILES
The script writes the following files into the selected output
directory:
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[CR]ca.key\f[R]
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[CR]ca.crt\f[R]
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[CR]ca.srl\f[R]
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[CR]<domain>.key\f[R]
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[CR]<domain>.csr\f[R]
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[CR]<domain>.crt\f[R]
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[CR]<domain>.pfx\f[R]
.SH EXAMPLES
.IP
.EX
selfcert
selfcert \-d example.local \-O certs
selfcert \-d example.local \-s www.example.local,api.example.local
selfcert \-d example.local \-o example\-ca \-y 825 \-O certs
selfcert \-d example.local \-p secret123
.EE
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
\f[B]0\f[R]
Success.
.TP
\f[B]1\f[R]
Invalid arguments, missing dependencies, or an OpenSSL failure occurred.
